#Text=Queenscliff
#Text=Queenscliff
#Text=( also known as Queenscliffe ) is an historic maritime community perched on a small spit of land in the south-eastern most corner of the Bellarine Peninsula .

#Text=Located in the South West Coast region of Victoria , the town was settled only a few years after Melbourne , and is characterised by its strong European heritage , maritime and seafaring character and its lasting connection to the sea .
#Text=The town is dotted with museums , grand hotels and also a fine variety of restaurants and eateries .
#Text=It is most known as the port of call of the Searoad Ferry , which connections the region to Portsea on the Mornington Peninsula .
#Text=This guide also covers the adjacent tourist resort of Point Lonsdale , a popular destination for family getaways with its splendid beach .
#Text=Understand
#Text=Queenscliffe Visitor Information Centre
#Text=, 55 Hesse St , ☏ +61352584843 , toll-free : 1300 884 843 , ✉ info.centre@queenscliffe.vic.gov.au .
#Text=9AM-5PM daily except Christmas Day .
#Text=By bus
#Text=McHarry ’s Buslines run from Geelong to the Bellarine Peninsula towns of Barwon Heads , Ocean Grove , Pt Lonsdale and Queenscliff ( 30 km ) .
#Text=By ferry
#Text=Car/passenger ferries cross the mouth of Port Phillip Bay between Queenscliff and Sorrento on Mornington Peninsula .
#Text=They depart each terminal on the hour every hour 7AM-6PM every day .
#Text=From 26 Dec. until end of daylight saving there are also 7PM sailings .

#Text=Foot passengers adult $ 10 , 5-15 years $ 8 , under 5 years $ 1 , foot passenger ’s bicycle $ 2 , tandem $ 3 ; passengers with vehicle adult $ 7.50 , 5-15 years $ 5.50 , under 5 years $ 1 ; vehicle rates vary with season – car up to 5.5m between $ 48 and $ 54 .
#Text=By bike
#Text=The Bellarine railtrail runs from South Geelong Station to Queenscliff .
#Text=Bike hire is available in Geelong from Geelong .
#Text=See
#Text=Fort Queenscliff
#Text=. was built in the 1880s as a defense against Russian invasion .
#Text=The Black Lighthouse is in its grounds .
#Text=There are guided tours at weekends and public holidays , adults $ 8 ? ? .
#Text=The fort is still a military establishment so you are required to sign in and show identification .
#Text=Queenscliff Maritime Museum
#Text=, 1 Weeroona Parade .
#Text=Bellarine Peninsula Railway
#Text=.
#Text=Steam trains run to Drysdale and return .
#Text=A number of impressive 19th century buildings remain , particularly along Gellibrand St.
#Text=Point Lonsdale
#Text=The headland is right at the entrance to Port Phillip Bay .
#Text=The channel through the heads is known as the Rip for its strong tidal currents .
#Text=There are short walks linking the Rip View Lookout , the pier and lighthouse .
#Text=Sleep
#Text=Vue Grand
#Text=A hotel with grand , heritage architecture and rooms .
#Text=Go next
#Text=Take the ferry to Sorrento or head to Geelong .
#Text=Alternatively drive or bus along the Great Ocean Road .
#Text=You do n’t need to drive through Geelong – from Barwon Heads take the Barwon Heads Rd which becomes Lower Duneed Rd then turn left onto the Surf Coast Highway .
